<dl id="n12004i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004i">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004i"> 4(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lanthorn visage / grandes</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">C&apos;&eacute;taient de <mark>grandes</mark> femmes, belles, v&ecirc;tues de blanc, et, selon l&apos;expression d&apos;un vieux paysan morbihannais &ldquo; si lumineuses, qu&apos;en regardant leurs figures, on croyait voir briller une lumi&egrave;re &agrave; travers une <mark>lanterne</mark> de corne&rdquo;. <br><font color="green">[They were tall and beautiful women, dressed in white and, according to the expression of an old Morbihan peasant &ldquo;so luminous that in looking at their faces one thought that one was looking at a light shining through a horn lantern&rdquo;]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 10</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
